results.description:

Narrow, rustic console table with hairpin legs, wooden rustic hallway table available in 2 wax colour finishes and with a choice of 5 leg colours and 2 leg heights.

Available in lengths from 45cm to 99cm maximum and depths from 14cm to 20cm (The depth of the one shown in the pictures is 16cm) 

To Order:

1. Height: Please select the leg height and leg colour from the first drop down menu. Choice of 71cm legs (overall height with shelf 75.5cm) or 86cm legs (90.5cm overall height with shelf)  PLEASE NOTE THE 71CM LEGS ARE 2 ROD HAIRPIN LEGS AND THE 86CM LEGS ARE 3 ROD HAIRPIN LEGS.

2. Length: Please select the correct 'up to' length and wood colour from the second drop down menu (for example if you would like a length of 67cm, please choose the up to 75cm option) THEN PLEASE ADD THE SPECIFIC LENGTH (e.g. 67cm length) to the order notes at checkout.

IF NO LENGTH IS SPECIFIED IN THE NOTES WE WILL SEND THE LONGEST LENGTH IN THE RANGE THAT YOU PAID FOR.
 
3.  Depth: Standard depth is 16cm but depths are available between 14cm (min) to 20cm (max) Please add a note to 'order notes' at checkout if you require a depth other than 16cm. IF NO DEPTH IS SPECIFIED IN THE NOTES WE WILL SEND AT 16CM DEEP.

****Please take the time to double check your measurements because every table is handmade to order and the legs are ordered separately for each individual order and because of this we are not able to accept returns or exchanges on correctly supplied items.*****

These rustic, chunky, wooden, narrow console tables are perfect for narrower hallways and landings with a depth of between 14cm and 20cm and will add a rustic, modern country charm to your home. 

Although the table is free standing it's not very stable like this so we provide a fixing to screw it to the wall. If you didn't want to screw into the wall 'No Damage Command Strips' (not provided) also work really well.

The unfinished raw steel leg option will start off with a shiny finish and then will naturally age and dull over a few weeks period.

Unlike other sellers we do not use old scaffold boards to make the tables. We only use brand new kiln dried timber (no risk of woodworm) and then carefully sand, smooth and prepare the surfaces before using our own special techniques to make the wood appear old and rustic. This is a very time consuming process and is the reason why we may be slightly more expensive. Please take the time to read our reviews of the hundreds of happy customers who have left us 5 star reviews.

Finished with a quality natural wax giving the narrow console table an aged finish whilst also protecting the wood and two steel hairpin legs.

Please note that due to the rustic nature of the wood all shelves may have slight differences in appearance and colour.
